<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 08 at 8:00PM EST  by NWS New York City - Upton</headline>
<description>There is potential for trace ice accretion if light rain develops
into the area by mid Sunday morning. Icy conditions on sidewalks,
roads and bridges would be possible. Be sure to check the
forecast and road conditions if you have travel plans Sunday
morning.
Temperatures should safely warm above freezing by around midday,
with any subsequent precipitation being plain rain.</description>
